  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "In a large bowl, combine shredded fernbrake, ground turkey, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.",
    "Stir until the mixture is evenly seasoned.",
    "Spread the mixture in a shallow baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes until the turkey is cooked through and the fernbrake is tender.",
    "Remove the dish from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Stir in low-fat yogurt, yuzu zest, and yuzu juice until the mixture is creamy and fluffy.",
    "Fold in chopped herbs gently.",
    "Transfer the fluffy mixture to a serving bowl, garnish with a sprinkle of fresh herbs.",
    "Serve warm; it can be paired with a side of steamed vegetables."
